16.name: Postcode directory
16.desc: [3251] Code defining postal zones or addresses.

37.name: Railway locations
37.desc: Code identifying a location in railway environment.

43.name: Clearing House Interbank Payment System Participants ID
43.desc: Participants identification of the automated clearing house of the New York Clearing House Association (CHIPS).

44.name: Clearing House Interbank Payment System Universal ID
44.desc: Universal identification of the automated clearing house of the New York Clearing House Association (CHAPS).

54.name: Statistical object
54.desc: A statistical object such as a statistical concept, array structure component or statistical nomenclature.

55.name: Quality conformance
55.desc: A code list specifying the quality standard a product complies with, e.g. ISO9000, BS5750, etc.

56.name: Safety regulation
56.desc: A code list specifying the safety regulations which apply to a product, such as UK COSHH (control of substances hazardous to health) regulations.

57.name: Product code
57.desc: Code assigned to a specific product by a controlling agency.

58.name: Business account number
58.desc: An identifying number or code assigned by issuing authorities to manage business activities.

59.name: Railway services harmonized code
59.desc: Services provided by the different railway organizations.

104.name: Customs area of transaction
104.desc: Customs code to indicate the different types of declarations according to the countries involved in the transaction (e.g. box 1/1 of SAD: inter EC Member States, EC-EFTA, EC-third countries, etc.).

105.name: Customs declaration type
105.desc: Customs code to indicate the type of declaration according to the different Customs procedures requested (e.g.: import, export, transit).

106.name: Incoterms 1980
106.desc: (4110) Code to indicate applicable Incoterm (1980 edition) under which seller undertakes to deliver merchandise to buyer (ICC). Incoterms 1990: use 4053 only.

107.name: Excise duty
107.desc: Customs or fiscal authorities code to identify a specific or ad valorem levy on a specific commodity, applied either domestically or at time of importation.

109.name: Customs indicator
109.desc: Customs code for circumstances where only an indication is needed.

110.name: Customs special codes
110.desc: Customs code to indicate an exemption to a regulation or a special Customs treatment.

112.name: Statistical nature of transaction
112.desc: Indication of the type of contract under which goods are supplied.

113.name: Customs office
113.desc: Customs administrative unit competent for the performance of Customs formalities, and the premises or other areas approved for the purpose by the competent authorities (CCC).

114.name: Railcar letter marking
114.desc: Codes for all marking codes (in letters) for railcars specifying the type, series, order number, check digit and some technical characteristics.

115.name: Examination facility
115.desc: Building or location where merchandise is examined by Customs.

116.name: Customs preference
116.desc: Customs code to identify a specific tariff preference.

117.name: Customs procedure
117.desc: (9380) Customs code to identify goods which are subject to Customs control (e.g. home use, Customs warehousing, temporary admission, Customs transit).

118.name: Government agency procedure
118.desc: Treatment applied by a government agency other than Customs to merchandise under their control.

119.name: Customs simplified procedure
119.desc: Customs code to indicate the type of simplified Customs procedure requested by a declarant (CCC).

120.name: Customs status of goods
120.desc: Customs code to specify the status accorded by Customs to a consignment e.g. release without further formality, present supporting documents for inspection, etc (CCC).

121.name: Shipment description
121.desc: Code to indicate whether a shipment is a total, part or split consignment.

122.name: Commodity
122.desc: (7357) Code identifying types of goods for Customs, transport or statistical purposes (generic term).

123.name: Entitlement
123.desc: Code to indicate the recipient of a charge amount (IATA).

125.name: Customs transit guarantee
125.desc: Customs code to identify the type of guarantee used in a transit movement.

126.name: Accounting information identifier
126.desc: Identification of a specific kind of accounting information.

127.name: Customs valuation method
127.desc: Customs code to identify the valuation method used to determine the dutiable value of the declared goods.

129.name: Customs warehouse
129.desc: Identification and/or location of the Customs warehouse in which goods will be or have been deposited (CCC).

130.name: Special handling
130.desc: Code to indicate that the nature of the consignment may necessitate use of special handling procedures (IATA).

131.name: Free zone
131.desc: Code identifying the zone within a state where any goods introduced are generally regarded, insofar as import duties and taxes are concerned, as being outside the Customs territory and are not subject to the usual Customs control.

132.name: Charge
132.desc: Identification of a type of charge.

133.name: Financial regime
133.desc: Nature and methods of a transaction from financial viewpoint.

134.name: Duty, tax or fee payment method
134.desc: [4390] Method by which a duty or tax is paid to the relevant administration.

135.name: Rate class
135.desc: Code to identify a specific rate category.

136.name: Restrictions/prohibitions on re-use of certain wagons

139.name: Port
139.desc: A location having facilities for means of transport to load or discharge cargo.

140.name: Area
140.desc: Codes for specific geographic areas e.g. seas, straits, basins etc.

143.name: Removable accessories and special equipment on railcars

145.name: Airport/city
145.desc: As described and published by IATA.

146.name: Means of transport identification
146.desc: Code identifying the name or number of a means of transport (vessel, vehicle).

147.name: Document requested by Customs
147.desc: Customs code to identify documents requested by Customs in an information interchange.

148.name: Customs release notification
148.desc: Authorisation given by Customs to move the goods or not move the goods from the place of registration.

149.name: Customs transit type
149.desc: Customs code to indicate the different kinds of transit movement of the goods (e.g. Box 1/3 of the SAD).

154.name: Bank branch sorting identification
154.desc: Identification of a specific branch of a bank.

156.name: Location of goods
156.desc: (3384) Indication of the place where goods are located and where they are available for examination.

157.name: Clearing code
157.desc: Identification of the responsible bank/clearing house which has cleared or is ordered to do the clearing.

158.name: Terms of delivery
158.desc: Code to identify terms of delivery.

161.name: Goods description
161.desc: Identification of a type of goods description.

163.name: Country sub-entity
163.desc: (3228) Identification of country sub-entity (region, department, state, province) defined by appropriate authority.

165.name: Amendment code (Customs)
165.desc: Customs code indicating the reason for transmitting an amendment to Customs.

166.name: Social security identification
166.desc: Code assigned by the authority competent to issue social security identification to identify a person.

167.name: Tax party identification
167.desc: Code assigned by a tax authority to identify a party.

169.name: Harmonized system
169.desc: Identification of commodities according to the Harmonized System.

173.name: Export requirements
173.desc: Identification of requirements and regulations established by relevant authorities concerning exportation.

176.name: Flow of the goods
176.desc: List of statistical codes covering the movement of the goods to be declared (e.g. despatch, arrival).

177.name: Statistical procedures
177.desc: Indication of the statistical procedure to which the goods are subject.

178.name: Standard text according US embargo regulations
178.desc: US government regulations prescribe specific standard text usage. Using codes from this code list prevents full text transmission.

179.name: Standard text for export according national prescriptions
179.desc: National export regulations prescribe specific standard text usage. Using codes from this code list prevents full text transmission.

180.name: Airport terminal
180.desc: Code identifying terminals or other sub-locations at airports.

182.name: Combiterms 1990
182.desc: Code to indicate the applicable Combiterm (1990 edition), used for the purpose of cost distribution between seller according to Incoterms 1990.

183.name: Dangerous goods packing type
183.desc: Identification of package types for the description related to dangerous goods.

184.name: Tax assessment method
184.desc: A code to identify the tax assessment method.

185.name: Item type
185.desc: A code list defining the level of elaboration of a item such as raw material, component, tooling, etc.

186.name: Product supply condition
186.desc: A code list specifying the rules according to which a product is supplied, e.g. from stock, available on demand, make on order, etc.

187.name: Supplier's stock turnover
187.desc: A code list giving an indication about the level of the supplier's stock turnover.

188.name: Article status
188.desc: A code list defining the status of an article from the procurement point of view, e.g. new article, critical article, etc.

189.name: Quality control code
189.desc: A code list specifying how the article is classified according to the quality control point of view, e.g. safety item, subject to regulation, etc.

190.name: Item sourcing category
190.desc: A code list to specify details related to the sourcing of the corresponding item such as provided by the buyer, from a mandatory source, etc.

191.name: Dumping or countervailing assessment method
191.desc: A code to identify the method used to determine the dumping or countervailing duty.

192.name: Dumping specification
192.desc: Code list to identify types of goods for dumping purposes.
